content:
Add Dynamic Images to Messaging Components

You can show different images depending on the situation by defining the images in the Messaging Component Builder using parameters or sObject formulas. Adding dynamic images to messaging components is more advanced than adding static images, but it’s an effective way to personalize messages sent to customers.

Available in: Lightning Experience
This article applies to: Messaging for In-App, Messaging for Web, enhanced WhatsApp, enhanced Facebook Messenger, enhanced SMS, enhanced Apple Messages for Business, and Bring Your Own Channel

To create messaging components:
Customize Application AND View Setup and Configuration
OR
System Administrator

To send and receive messages in Messaging:
Messaging Agent

When an agent or bot sends a messaging component with dynamic images, Salesforce provides the right images based on parameters that you set.

Provide Images via an Image ID Parameter

Here are the high-level steps to add dynamic images to messaging components with image ID parameters:

Create the messaging component in Setup.
Add one or more supported formats to the component.
Update each format’s image properties to use image parameters.
Click a format name and select the Parameters type and select an image parameter.
On the Flows page in Setup, create a screen flow that agents can run to send the messaging component to a customer.

Provide Images via a MESSAGINGIMAGE Formula

You can instead provide the image dynamically with a MESSAGINGIMAGE formula. It contains two parameters: imageUrl and mimeType. The formula takes this format: MESSAGINGIMAGE(imageUrl, mimeType).
title: Adding Dynamic Images to Salesforce Service Cloud Messaging Components
